The parents of the siblings contacted the police when they realised the pair had vanished over the weekend. JOHANNESBURG - A man linked to the abduction of two young children in Soweto is expected to appear in the Protea Magistrates Court on Monday.The parents of the siblings, aged four and five, contacted the police when they realised the pair had vanished over the weekend.The children were found unharmed a short while later.The police's Mpande Khoza says, He is currently in the police cells and will appear in the Protea Magistrates Court, where he will face two charges of kidnapping. We re not aware of the motive behind this. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)